title: The Writer's Almanac -  Saturday, January 25, 2020
description: It’s the birthday of Virginia Woolf (1882), who began writing professionally in her early 20s after a mental breakdown. Her novels include Mrs Dalloway (1925) and To the Lighthouse (1927).
